extends ./layout.pug
block content
  // navbar
  nav.navbar.navbar-expand-md.navbar-light.justify-content-between.fixed-top
    a.navbar-brand(href='/')
      img.logo.my-2(src='../img/logo_edited1.png' alt='logo')
    button.navbar-toggler(type='button' data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#navbarsExampleDefault' aria-controls='navbarsExampleDefault' aria-expanded='false' aria-label='Toggle navigation')
      span.navbar-toggler-icon
    #navbarsExampleDefault.collapse.navbar-collapse.justify-content-end
      ul.navbar-nav
        li.nav-item.active
          a.nav-link(href='/')
            | Home
            span.sr-only (current)
        li.nav-item
          a.nav-link(href='/about') About
        li.nav-item
          a.nav-link(href='/menu') Menu
        li.nav-item
          a.nav-link(href='/services') Services
        li.nav-item
          a.nav-link(href='/contact') Contact
        li.nav-item
          a.nav-link(href='/register') Register
        li.nav-item
          a.nav-link(href='/login') Login
      .ml-3.top-search
        // util search
        form.form-inline(method='get' action='')
          input(type='hidden' name='_token' value='')
          input#query.form-control.searchbox(type='search' name='query' placeholder='Search')
          //- i.material-icons.searchbox__icon Search
          span.input-group-btn
            button.btn.btn-outline-info.my-2.my-sm-0.text-white.bu(type='submit') Search
      .menu-top-wrapper
        .ml-3.acct_user.d-flex
          // util profile
          a(href='/profile')
            .circle1
              .user_image
                i.fas.fa-user-alt.text-white
        .ml-2.acct_srch.d-flex
          // shopping cart
          .ml-2.circle
            a(href='/cart')
              i.fas.fa-shopping-cart.text-white
  // /navbar
  // jumbotron
  .jumbotron.jumbotron-fluid.bg-info.text-black
    .container.text-sm-center.pt-5
      h1#frosted.display-2
        | Eritrean Traditional Food
        p.food Enjoy Eritrean traditional spicy food with (injera) flat bread
        .btn-group.mt-4(role='group' aria-label='Callout buttons')
          a.btn.btn-danger.js-scroll-trigger(href='/menu') Order Here
  // /jumbotron
  .container.pt-4
    // about
    #about.row
      .col-lg.order-lg-2
        h3.mb-4 About Eritrea
        img.mb-4.img-fluid.rounded.d-none.d-sm-block(src='../img/asmara_cathedral.jpg' alt='Asmara')
        p
          | Eritrea is a northeast African country on the 
          a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eritrea' target='_blank') Red Sea coast.
          |  It shares borders with Ethiopia, Sudan and Djibouti.
        p
          | The capital city, Asmara, is known for its Italian colonial
          | buildings, like St.Joseph&apos;s Cathedral, as well as art deco structures.
        p
          | Italian, Egyptian and Turkish architecture in Massawa reflect the port city&apos;s colorful history.
      .col-lg.order-lg-1
        h3.mb-4 Eritrean Cuisine
        img.mb-4.img-fluid.rounded.d-none.d-sm-block(src='../img/cuisine.jpg' alt='Eritrean Food')
        p
          | The main traditional food in Eritrean cuisine is tsebhi (stew), served with injera (flatbread made from teff, wheat, or sorghum
          | and hilbet (paste made from legumes; mainly lentil and fava beans)
        p
          | A typical traditional Eritrean dish consists of injera accompanied by a spicy stew, which frequently includes beef, goat, lamb or fish.
      .col-lg.order-lg-3
        h3.mb-4 How To Eat Eritrean Food
        img.mb-4.img-fluid.rounded.d-none.d-sm-block(src='../img/enjera.jpg' alt='Eritrean Food')
        p
          a(href='/about') Taita,
          | also known as injera, is much more than a piece of bread. It also serves as a plate and cutlery!
        p
          | Eating with your hand might sound messy, but it&rsquo;s easy when you have a big piece of taita (flat bread) that you
          | can use to scoup up the stews and vegetables from your plate to your mouth.
    hr
    .row
      .col-12
        h4.mb-4 Most Prefered Dishes
          .list-group
            ol
              li Geat(Porrage)
              li Zigni(Beaf Stew)
              li Shiro(spiced powedered chikpea)
            dl
              dt Bun(Coffee) Preparation
              dd
                | Wash the coffee beans in cool water. Pick through them like just like you would any other bean, removing
                | any yucky looking specimens
              dd
                | Pour off extra water and roast the beans in pan over medium/medium-low until popping and dark brown. Keep shaking the pan.
              dd
                | Grind the beans and brew it in a 
                b Jebena(coffe pot)
                |  for about 10-15 minutes then let it rest for few minutes
                |                             until the coffee ground rest at the bottom then pour it in a 
                b Finjal(coffee cup).
  // footer area
  footer.text-center.text-white
    // Grid container
    .container.pt-4
      // Section: Social media
      section.mb-4
        // Instagram
        a.btn.btn-primary.btn-floating.m-1(style='background-color: #ac2bac;' href='https://www.instagram.com/rahwa_netsereab/' role='button')
          i.fab.fa-instagram
        
        // Linkedin
        a.btn.btn-primary.btn-floating.m-1(style='background-color: #0082ca;' href='https://www.linkedin.com/in/rahwa-mehreteab/' role='button')
          i.fab.fa-linkedin-in
        
        // Github
        a.btn.btn-primary.btn-floating.m-1(style='background-color: #333333;' href='https://github.com/Rahwa-n' role='button')
          i.fab.fa-github
        
        br
        br
        a.mail.text-white(href='mailto:rahwa@example.com?subject=About the traditional food')
          i.fa.fa-envelope(style='font-size:24px;')
          | Click here to send us an email
      // Section: Social media
    // Grid container
    // <hr>
    // Copyright
    .text-.text-white.p-3
      | Copyright &copy; Eritrean Traditional Food 2021
  
